==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1548|1548]], from [[Late Latin]] [[perspicacitas]] ''discernment'', from [[Latin]] [[perspicax]] ''sharp-sighted'', from [[perspicere]] "look through", from [[per-]] ''through'' + [[specere]] ''look at''. See also [[perspective]].
===Adjective===
#Having the power of seeing clearly; quick-sighted; sharp of sight.
#(''[[figurative]]'') Of acute [[discernment]]; [[keen]]; mentally perceptive.
